dcterms:description: The Branin function is a well-known test function for optimization algorithms, defined over the domain [0, 1]^2. It has multiple local minima and is often used to evaluate the performance of optimization methods.
dcterms:title: Branin function

dcterms:creator: J. Azimi
A. Jalali
X. Z. Fern
dcterms:description: The Hartmann-4D function is a four-dimensional test function used for optimization, characterized by its complex landscape with multiple local minima. It is defined over the domain [0, 1]^4.
dcterms:title: Hartmann-4D function

dcterms:creator: J. Azimi
A. Jalali
X. Z. Fern
dcterms:description: The Hartmann-6D function is a six-dimensional test function for optimization, known for its challenging landscape with several local minima. It is defined over the domain [0, 1]^6.
dcterms:title: Hartmann-6D function
